init_text: Following World War III, all the nations of the world agreed to 50 years of strict isolation from one another in order to prevent additional conflicts. 50 years later, the United States comes out of exile, only to learn that no one else went into isolation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Crime is rampant, and most of the world's nations are run by dictators.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Civilization as we know it has collapsed.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is under the dictatorial control of a man named President Hudson, who has begun to advocate for his own dictatorship over all of

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: President Hudson's control is challenged by an uprising in the Rocky Mountains, led by a man named David Sawyer.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer's army includes his partner, Nate Madock; his lover, Kate Warner; former girlfriend, Anne Matheson (who is also a CIA

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The United States is in a state of turmoil, with the President's loyalists centered in New York City and the rebels based out of Idaho

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The resistance begins small, with Sawyer's rebels attacking critical infrastructure and government targets, but soon becomes a full-scale war.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In a last ditch effort to quell the uprising, President Hudson orders the use of nuclear weapons on Sawyer's stronghold in Idaho.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer and his army escape the nuclear blast, but are trapped underground.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: While in the caves, David and Kate uncover the message of a long-dead man known as The Prophet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Prophet's message calls people to action, to rise up against corrupt governments and oppressive regimes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The resistance eventually re-emerges to challenge President Hudson.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The resistance makes contact with other resistance movements around the globe, and they unite under the banner of The Prophet.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The Prophet's technology includes the ability to create self-replicating nanobots, that can be used as super weapons.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The resistance, now unified, uses the nanobots to attack New York City.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The nanobots attack by targeting the city's infrastructure, and cause the city to plunge into darkness.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The President and his forces are left powerless without electricity.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The city's people, who are now starving and freezing, rise up against the President.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Meanwhile, Sawyer's forces attack the United Nations building in New York City, targeting President Hudson.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Hudson attempts to escape, but Sawyer captures him.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer brings the President to the United Nations in New York City, where Sawyer's forces have taken control of the building.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer puts President Hudson on trial for crimes against humanity.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Following the trial, Sawyer leads his army to ZÃ¼rich, Switzerland.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer's forces attack a secret compound in Switzerland, and release another hologram from storage.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The hologram is of the Prophet's daughter, and she offers Sawyer more technology, including a supercomputer that has the entire sum of human knowledge and

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Sawyer and his army learn from the supercomputer that Earth is heading for a disaster.
